{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2ed40b58-a602-4e0d-b5df-65b751c8fff7","content":"Here's how to use HotReload to iterate quickly:\n\n**Run `dotnet test` with the `--hotreload` flag:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in watch mode. When you save changes to your code, it **hot-reloads** the updated code and re-runs the tests — no full rebuild needed.\n\n**Your current situation:** `IsValidEmail` only checks for non-empty strings but doesn't check for `@`, so `Validate_MissingAtSign_ReturnsFalse` will fail. With hot-reload running, you can fix the method and see the results immediately on save.\n\nFor example, fix line 27 to:\n\n```csharp\nreturn !string.IsNullOrEmpty(email) && email.Contains('@');\n```\n\nSave the file, and the test runner will automatically re-run with the updated logic — no need to restart.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f8ca8cd6-dc18-4f51-bfd0-78f963d0f579","outputTokens":214,"requestId":"4C52:3434CB:C02CD6:EEDEE8:6A013290"},"id":"a16ad11d-586b-40f6-90e8-a8843c90f80b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:36:23.343Z","parentId":"703796bb-b347-492d-8319-1f32157651f7"}
